description: Jack Frost, all things being equal, is a much better hero than his dad. You want monsters? We got 'em! You want quests and riches? We got 'em in spades! You want fish men from Venus? Well...we don't actually have those.
name: Lessons Learned, Some More Enjoyable than Others: Kings of Earth and Sky, Part Three of Five

description: The "Ghosts" storyline written and drawn by Sam Kieth continues with part 3 of 4! Batman and Callie become closer as they literally share their troubles when Batman goes blind! And the creature they're fighting continues taking the two down memory lane. But can either Batman or Callie handle being forced to face the loss of their parents?
name: Ghosts, Part 3

description: Death could not stop him! Shamballah has been destroyed, Deimos is resurrected and The Warlord is...defeated? A hero will die - but will the legend live on? The coming months will reveal all as DC's finest fantasy epic throws away the rulebook and takes a turn you never saw coming!
name: Sunset

description: Billy Tucci (SGT. ROCK: THE LOST BATTALION) saddles up to illustrate the latest HEX! What person connects a coffin, a train robbery, a wicked double-crossing, and a wannabe-actress-turned-saloon-dancer? You know his name. It's right there in the title. But he knows yours, too, so you better buy the book - or else...
name: You'll Never Dance Again

description: Hail Galactus, Herald to the Son of the Hulk?! As the SON OF HULK, Hiro-Kala, sets loose a chain of events that forever alters Jarella's World and threatens the entire sub-atomic Microverse, a vision reveals his future metamorphosis into a god-like being, with an enslaved Galactus at his control! As his dark destiny unfolds, Commander Rann and Princess Mari arrive on the planet K'ai, as Rann's obsessive quest to find an Enigma Force cure to his deadly radiation disease finally takes it's toll… but are they too late? BOOK II of “THE CONQUEST OF JARELLA’S WORLD”
name: The Conquest Of Jarella's World, Book II

volume.name: Realm of Kings Son of Hulk

description:
The All-Stars are forced to team with the Injustice Society against Johnny Sorrow's unearthly accomplice! And only Star Girl knows what she must sacrifice to save friend and foe alike!

The hero and villain team-ups continue in the co-feature, as Liberty Belle and Hourman join their proven enemies Tigress and Icicle, who hold essential clues as to the whereabouts of the ancient mysticism embodied in the Staff of Life!
name: Stellar Collapse: Constellations, Part Three; The Inheritance, Part Three: Let's Make A Deal!

description: Panamaraibo, Suriname. Here, Mister No meets his old companion in arms: Pieter Bogghedal, called Bog. His friend tells him how, years before, he fell in love with Lupe Herreira, an attractive girl who was much richer than him; to avoid a feeling of inferiority, Bog decided to get hold of a large sum of money. In an illegal way…
name: La Donna del Mistero

description: Bog had committed a robbery for love of Lupe, but he was wounded and captured by the police. Sentenced to nine years in prison, he learned from his lawyer that Lupe had died, she had been murdered. Released from prison, Bog wants Mister No to help him find Lupe’s killer…
name: Il Tesoro Scomparso

description: Mister No investigates Lupe’s death, helped by his beautiful girlfriend Olivia de Vere. Where is the money that Bog stole? Who is the beautiful wife of the lawyer Felix? Jerry’s path is littered with corpses and the truth will be bitter for Bog. So bitter that our pilot prefers to lie to him…
name: L'Assassino nell'Ombra

description: The Pantanal is a huge wild marshy region at the border between Brazil, Bolivia and Paraguay. Mister No crosses it following his client, Raffles, who has to write a scientific report on the Pantanal. Thus, Jerry boards the “Rosa Dos Ventos”, which however is famed for being a ship with a curse on it…
name: Sfida al Pantanal

description: Mister No and his companions immediately run into the ferocious Panatal, but also into the savage wilderness of nature and the savagery of men like the cruel Manuale Brandao, known as “Zagaiero” (from the weapon used for capturing jaguars, a short assegai), who attempts to kill him. And he also encounters the “Coureiros”, the caiman hunters that kidnap women….
name: Zagaieiro!

description: The liberation of the women kidnapped by the “Coureiros” is successful, but the debt to pay in blood is high. The Pantanal has already asked the men of “Rosa Dos Ventos” for the first victims. Mister No and Raffles are then invited as guests of the rich Fazendeiro Getulio Vieira, and the pilot is attracted to his beautiful daughter Selma. But it would have been better not to trust Vieira…
name: Un Mondo Violento

description: After sending them to sleep with a powerful sleeping potion, Getulio Vieira has captured Mister No and Raffles, and he has handed them over to Zagaieiro, but the pair, thanks to the Rosa Dos Ventos men, are able to escape. Their troubles, however, are far from over…
name: Lo Spettro del Rio Cuiabà

description: A ghost! The “Rosa Dos Ventos” men think it is similar to Captain Teixiera brought back to life. Having survived the piranhas that have disfigured his face horrendously, Teixeira lets loose the Cadiveus Indios against our men!
name: Viaggio all'Inferno

description: Eight quintals of gold have been extracted secretly, in the Amazon, by the Forbes Rubber Company. Guarding it are four gallows-birds: Boris (an old friend of Mister No’s), Karl Pachino (Audrey’s husband, a friend of Mister No), Ugarte and Klaus. The four have sunk the gold in the river and now they want to recover it. But Karl has been killed: who else knows about the gold?
name: L'Oro del Fiume

description: Mister No dives to recover the chests of gold that have been in a boat on the seabed for years, but he discovers they are empty! Doubt taints the group : is there a traitor among them? Little by little, all the components are mysteriously killed, and even Mister No ends up in a deep coma!
name: Il Nemico Senza Nome

description: Mexico. The medic of the Jalapa prison, Benito Torres, badly wounded, dies after having said a few words to Mister No, who tried to revive him. Many want to find out from Jerry - even by force - what the medic said to him, but our hero keeps his mouth shut. Following Torres’s indications he goes to the Yucatán to join the Anthropologist Santiago Lucas…
name: Veracruz!

description: Inside a “cenote”, that is to say, a sacred ancient Mayan well, a treasure is hidden. People are looking for it - Mister No, the anthropologist Santiago Lucas and the beautiful Consuelo Ibanez, who hides a secret: her father was Fernando Valdez, a small landowner who found a rich “cenote” and tattooed the map on his daughter’s neck!
name: Il Pozzo dei Sacrifici

description: Art sensation Andy Clarke (R.E.B.E.L.S., BATMAN CONFIDENTIAL) joins writer Grant Morrison for an exciting three-issue arc titled "Batman vs. Robin"! Why would Talia al Ghul manipulate her son Damian into taking action against Batman? Will Damian do as Mother says…or stay loyal to Dick Grayson? Plus, more on the Domino Killer, Oberon Sexton, and the menace of El Penitente's drug cartel! Is this already the end for the new Dynamic Duo?
name: Batman vs. Robin, Part 1: The Haunting of Wayne Manor

description: A lurid tell-all book leads the Punisher on the trail of a hitwoman marked for death. Who is Butterfly? And will the Punisher be her salvation, her temptation, or her damnation? Author Valerie D'Orazio and artist Laurence Campbell unload a full barrage of mayhem in this blood-soaked one-shot.
name: Butterfly

description:
"Writer's Blockheads": Ms. Grundy decides to have the class collaborate on a story by having each write a section. The theme is spring, but somewhere along the line the story turns into an adventure about rampaging robots, a romance where Reggie is the lead Romeo, and a quest to find the perfect burger!

"Memory Lapse": Betty and Veronica are astonished when they witness a hapless boy caught between two girlfriends in a loopy love triangle... they can't even imagine such a thing!
name: Writer's Blockheads

description: Published by Panini

"Battle of the Bots": Jughead doesn't make the basketball team as his parents hope, but Dilton and Chuck convince Jughead that his imagination would make him a formidable teammate on the robotics team. Can Jughead's unique intelligence help machines with artificial intelligence score baskets?"A Pair with Flair": In a follow-up to the previous story, the robotics team takes on various other problems at Riverdale High - like school budget cuts in the maintenance and cafeteria crews, tardy students and more. But have they created a Frankenstein's monster in the process?
name: Battle of the Bots
